fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.views

Interface IListView


  • public interface IListView
    Provides default or customized access to views of data lists for a specific user and a master data source.

    To maintain state between requests, the view definition may be exported and then re-imported using a serialized format, without requiring management of on-disk or in-memory resources (the definition can be passed to the client if suitable integrity checks are applied).

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe: customizations are obtained using the adapt method, and may be persisted using the store method.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IListViewFilter, IListFetchFilter, IDataViewService.getListViews(ticket)

    • Method Detail

      • toList

        IList toList(long rangeOffset)
      throws AuthzException,
             ListFetchException
        Fetches a list matching the current view definition, starting from the specified item index. The filter and sort are applied.
        Parameters:
        rangeOffset - index of the first item in the range to fetch. This is not the page number: this is the index of the first item (starting with 0, relative to the sort order and filter).
        Returns:
        the matching list, where the number of returned items is limited to the page item count. May return an empty list, but never null.
        Throws:
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        toPage(int), IListFetchFilter.beforeDataListFetch(IListView)

      • toPage

        IList toPage(int pageNumber)
      throws AuthzException,
             ListFetchException
        Fetches a list matching the current view definition, for the specified page number. The filter and sort are applied.
        Parameters:
        pageNumber - the number of the page, starting with 1, used to determine the range of items that may be returned. The contents of the page will depend up on the current sort order and the current filter.
        Returns:
        the matching list, where the number of returned items is limited to the page item count. May return an empty list, but never null.
        Throws:
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        toList(long), IListFetchFilter.beforeDataListFetch(IListView)

      • getPageCount

        long getPageCount(long itemsPerPage)
           throws AuthzException,
                  FetchException
        Determines the number of pages required to include all items, for the specified number of items per page, when the current filter is applied.
        Parameters:
        itemsPerPage - the number of items per page, used to determine the number of pages relative to the available number of items, and taking into consideration the current filter.
        Returns:
        the number of pages, where zero indicates "no data".
        Throws:
        AuthzException - if the user does not have sufficient privileges.
        ListFetchException - if the fetch fails.
        FetchException
        Since:
        1.0

      • getMasterSource

        default ISource getMasterSource()
        Gets the master data source used to provide data elements based on this effective settings of this list view instance.

        Merged lists may include multiple sources, so this is the reference source (the starting point for accessing related data). The effective structure is described as the fetch souce.

        Returns:
        the non-null master source.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getFetchSource(), toList(long)

      • getFetchSource

        IFetchable getFetchSource()
        Gets the effective data source used to provide data elements based on this effective settings of this list view instance.

        This may be identical to the master source, or may be a derived intersection (merged view of multiple sources). Generally, an intersection is necessary when resolving foreign key constraints or when applying relational boolean algebra.

        Returns:
        the non-null effective data source. Identical to the source for derived lists.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getFetchableCells()

      • getDisplayableCells

        SortedSet<ICell> getDisplayableCells()
        Gets the ordered set of displayable cells in the list. The returned list is the same as, or a subset of, the list of fetchable cells; violating this constraint is an error.
        Returns:
        the non-null collection of displayable cells, which must be the same as, or a subset of, the collection of fetchable cells. Returning an empty collection is possible but of no practical use.
        Since:
        1.0

      • adapt

        IListView adapt(IFilter filter,
                ISort sort,
                SortedSet<ICell> fetchableCells,
                SortedSet<ICell> displayableCells,
                int pageItemCount)
        Adapts the current view to be able to modify the filter, the sorting behavior, and the ordered list of displayable cells.
        Parameters:
        filter - the new filter definition to use. If null, the current filter is implied.
        sort - the new sort definition to use. If null, the current sort is implied.
        fetchableCells - the new set of fetchable cells to use. If null, the current set is implied. It is of no practical use to specify an empty set.
        displayableCells - the new set of displayable cells to use. If null, the current set is implied. It is of no practical use to specify an empty set. Additional displayable cells defined for the adapted view will be added automatically to the set of fetchable cells.
        pageItemCount - the number of items per page (defines the list's range relative to a page number, specified when fetching). The current count is obtained using getPageItemCount().
        Returns:
        the adapted copy instance.
        Since:
        1.0
